title: Terminal Emulator for Android
comment: This app has allowed me to discover much about the inner workings of Android devices They all differ. Use gzip on files to really squash them down even on unrooted devices. Use gunzip  to get them back. The emulator works best with Hacker's Keyboard (free). Use the cp command to copy files from internal memory to the sdcard. Use df to find block devices (drives) . Type the word "busybox" and read how Android uses one file to implement  numerous commands. On many devices another binary, "toolbox", replaces busybox. It does not give useful information when its name is typed. I found this app on f-droid first and Google Play second. I've used it on several Androids. If you know Linux this app can keep you busy for hours. Many of the negative comments are from users who do not realize some d things require ROOT. Not all commands are on all devices. Some devices, for intance, lack the cp command. The fault is the device NOT the app.
